ProtoTheorem:
. "Let $D$ be an integral domain and let $a, b \in D$. Then
\begin{enumerate}
  \item $a \mid b \Leftrightarrow \langle b \rangle \subset \langle a \rangle$. \item $a$ and $b$ are associates $\Leftrightarrow$ $\langle b \rangle =
\langle a \rangle$.
  \item $a$ is a unit in $D$
$\Leftrightarrow$ $\langle a \rangle = D$.
\end{enumerate}"
